  "prompt": "Is the driver job in Uber considered as work experience when applying for higher studies abroad?",
  "response": "Yes, being a driver for Uber can be considered work experience when applying for higher studies abroad, especially if the application requires you to list all your professional experiences. When showcasing your experience, you should emphasize relevant skills you developed in the role, such as customer service, time management, problem-solving, and any leadership or entrepreneurial skills if you operated as an independent contractor. \n\nAdditionally, if your desired field of study relates to areas such as business, logistics, hospitality, or urban studies, your experience as a driver can provide a unique perspective and practical knowledge relevant to those fields. Just be sure to explain how this experience has prepared you for further studies and aligns with your academic and professional goals.",
